<subSubSection id="C81771B92F15D3D6E8E9CB84D80E12DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="BFD7C0A8D0A9F0E6537CCD5D03B35767" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EA3B659D1753AA47DED7920EB3C2788" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="1CB53D124052873F4E0482E3007C2F4C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum involucratum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="involucratum">
<emphasis id="712C567828E1E4DA62E4EBB77463D9B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum involucratum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a plant of tropical evergreen or deciduous rainforest, it grows on limestone or on clay soil, also in secondary forests; from 50 to 1,400 m elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
